        <section id="reality" class="bg-white rounded-xl card-shadow border border-stone-100 p-8">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Standards of Practice: Law vs. Reality</h3>
            
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                <!-- Card 1 -->
                <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-stone-200">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                        <span class="text-xl mr-2">üëî</span>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800">The "Manager" Trap</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-sm space-y-3">
                        <p><strong class="text-amber-700">Regulation:</strong> You must have a qualified manager with 5 years experience to apply.</p>
                        <p><strong class="text-slate-700">Reality:</strong> This is a "Catch-22". You have to hire (and pay) this person for the 6-12 months while you wait for the license, with zero revenue coming in. Most founders offer equity or "signing bonuses" to keep them on board during the wait.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 2 -->
                <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-stone-200">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                        <span class="text-xl mr-2">üîé</span>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800">Background Checks</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-sm space-y-3">
                        <p><strong class="text-amber-700">Regulation:</strong> Officers, directors, and shareholders (10%+) must be fingerprinted (Live Scan).</p>
                        <p><strong class="text-slate-700">Reality:</strong> The DFPI digs deep. An old DUI or minor financial blemish from 10 years ago can delay your application by 3 months. Disclose <em>everything</em> upfront. Surprises = Rejections.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 3 -->
                <div class="bg-stone-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-stone-200">
                    <div class="flex items-center mb-3">
                        <span class="text-xl mr-2">üõ°Ô∏è</span>
                        <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800">EAFC Membership</h4>
                    </div>
                    <div class="text-sm space-y-3">
                        <p><strong class="text-amber-700">Regulation:</strong> Membership in Escrow Agents' Fidelity Corporation is mandatory.</p>
                        <p><strong class="text-slate-700">Reality:</strong> This is the final boss. Even if DFPI approves you, EAFC can deny coverage if they don't like your financials or manager. Without EAFC, you cannot open.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

